Text.Value: I will heed my companions' needs - I would not have made it this far without them.
I will reap a savage fate on this world unlike any that has ever been seen.
March. Join my power.
First, I will save my father. Nothing else matters right now.
*And what then? You are prone to impulses as uncontrollable as the gods themselves. Will you even have a say in what you do?*
When the moment comes, I'll do what feels right.
*Lady Shar sent you on this mission - did she know that this is where it would lead?*
*That you remain alive is a failure to Mystra. But if you were to lay hands on that Crown... might she have reason to forgive you then? Would you even need her forgiveness?*
I will free everyone of this evil - I will be the one to cleanse this plane of the Absolute.
I will free everyone of this evil - I will be the hero that saves Baldur's Gate.
*The very same visitor who Vlaakith seems so eager to kill.*
*The very same visitor who Vlaakith seems so eager to kill - and Voss seems so eager to free.*
Hear me. Gather. The reckoning is upon us.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [KAYLEIGH] Player laying on the ground awakens suddenly and clutches their head in pain while rolling on the ground.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Booming sounds of the voice of the Absolute throughout this dialogue and into gameplay. Player awakes suddenly, clutching their head in pain, rolling on the ground.

Text.Value: *Even as you utter the words to yourself, you know it is but an intention. And these dark desires of yours have little regard for your intentions.*
*You know servitude better than anyone - you have been denied freedom for nearly two centuries, and are denied it still.*
*Together, you have the power to thwart the Dead Three. If you follow this path to its end, the elder brain will not answer to the Chosen. It will answer to you.*
*You who are a plaything for a cambion.*
*This would have been your fate too, were it not for the dream visitor's protection.*
*Will you liberate the True Souls from their parasites and their religious delusions? Or will you use the power you gain for your own purposes?*
*This would have been your fate too, were it not for the Astral Prism and the mysterious visitor inside of it.*
I will have my vengeance. Cazador will be dust.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [KAYLEIGH] MoCap - Player gets blinded by the light and looks away, lifting their hand in front of their face trying to shield from it., Keyframe - The artefact floating in the air, cracks in it shifting and opening up.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
The cracks in the artefact light up, shafts of light splintering out of it, blinding the player as a portal forms. 

Some of Orpheus' githyanki guard appear out of the portal, braced for combat.
EditorData.SFXTags: [KD] magic humming intenses and then bursts into a flash of light creating a portal
EditorData.VFXTags: [KD] Light busts/flashes magic light off artifact creating a portal

Text.Value: *If the dream visitor speaks true, then the entire Sword Coast is under threat. It will take a true hero to save it. But is that really you?*
*The events of the last days weigh heavily upon you. Sleep's rest is slow to come to one whose mind is so full.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player lying down in bedroll, contemplating while trying to fall asleep.

Text.Value: *A thrill courses through you at the thought.*
I will confront the Mother Superior and her Sharran lackeys. Then I will free my parents.
I will continue in Lady Shar's service. She will never know a more loyal follower. Nor a stronger one.
*All who carry the tadpole are governed by the brain, and by extension, the Chosen. It will take but one order to transform them into an army of mind flayers.*
*With her help, you have uncovered the cult for what it really is - a plan of conquest orchestrated by the gods of death themselves.*
*With his help, you have uncovered the cult for what it really is - a plan of conquest orchestrated by the gods of death themselves.*
*With their help, you have uncovered the cult for what it really is - a plan of conquest orchestrated by the gods of death themselves.*
*Right now, your resolve feels firm. But there is no knowing how you will feel when the moment comes.*
*And what role will you play?*
I've witnessed the Heart of the Absolute. I'm going the learn the secrets of that crown...
I will do as Voss asked. I will protect the Astral Prism and free the one inside.
All I want is to be free of this parasite. I will do what is necessary to make that happen.
First, Gortash. Then, the rest of my life.
*Your blood swims hot at the very prospect.*
I will find a way to rid myself of these disturbing impulses.
*You are hungry beyond blood, beyond lust, beyond your unliving life itself.*
*And when you complete it, what will you do then?*
*The Absolute is not a god, but an elder brain controlled by the Chosen of the Dead Three. They mean to use it to take control of the Sword Coast.*
*A heavy burden indeed. After all, the artefact that protects you came from your own people. What role have they to play in this plane's existence?*
*You will not have long to wait. All you need to do now is sleep...*
*And what of the True Souls? Will you liberate them from their parasites and religious delusions? Or will you use the power for your own gain?*
*Will you liberate them from their parasites and their religious delusions? Or will you use the power you gain for your own purposes?*
I will succeed where the Chosen will fail. I will dominate the world.
*But sleep is not for you.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player is abruptly woken up by the pain in their head from the booming voice of the Absolute.

Text.Value: *And what of your father? Will you tear him away from the elder brain's clutches, or allow him to suffer?*
The city thirsts for domination.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [KAYLEIGH] MoCap - The player reaches for the artefact but can't lift themself off the ground., Keyframe - The artefact levitates into the air, glowing shaking, rattling, as if fighting something.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The artefact levitates into the air, glowing shaking, rattling, as if fighting something. The player reaches for it but can't lift themself off the ground.
EditorData.SFXTags: [KD] Magic light Artifact lights up Puzzel box makes a humming sound

Text.Value: *You will finally have the chance to destroy Gortash. But what then? What fires will still burn in you when he is extinguished?*
*You who bear the face of a devil.*
I will fulfil my duty to my queen. I will ascend!

Synopsis:
The players are woken up by the booming voice of the Absolute becoming unbearable. The artefact struggles and eventually shines bright, opening a portal (seen in gameplay) to the Astral Plane.

 GROUP_Players in SpeakerGroup1 is the active player.
